verbose_text: We also showed that diabetic AAs and Hispanics had a higher prevalence of early CKD compared with whites, and we found higher levels of UAE in AAs and Hispanics, higher absolute CRP levels in AAs, and an association between CRP and UAE in AAs and Hispanics (stronger in Hispanics), providing additional evidence for a role of inflammation in the increased prevalence of early diabetic CKD in both ethnic groups.
